        <abstract>
            <p>Galapagos land birds and reptiles.</p>
            <p>No two naturalists agree on any fundamental idea [of species]. "Everything is arbitrary."</p>
            <p>Has been with Richard Owen going over the S. American fossils.</p> 
<p>Has worked out the <hi rend="italic">non</hi>-relation between animals’ bulk and luxuriance of vegetation.</p> 
            <p>The horse once common on the Pampas. The mystery of the extinction of these animals.</p>
        </abstract>
